Hey guys, so I came across someone calling me a rather interesting name, a &quot;norm hero&quot; as in &quot;normals hero&quot;. I just had a game where as Lee Sin I did &#039;relatively well&#039; ending the game 4/2/4 and helping our Yas get a Quadra etc, when suddenly Rengar (enemy jungler) asked me if I was a &quot;normals hero&quot; seeing that I have around 1600 normal wins but have little to no progress/history in ranked at all. I mean as an extremely casual player I actually quite like the term &quot;norm hero&quot; even though &quot;hero&quot; exaggerates my 4/2/4 score which isn&#039;t insanely great anyway (I mean our Yasuo got a quadra, he should be the hero but eh). I&#039;ve been playing since Sept 2012 and have always been a casual player but this is the first time I&#039;ve been called that.

What do you guys think? He said I should start to climb out of Bronze even though I&#039;m worse; I&#039;ve been essentially unranked for 3 seasons now.

{{sticker:slayer-jinx-catface}}
